optimum data base reorganization points.win certain data base organization schemes thecost per access may increase due to structural inefficiencies caused by updates.  by reorganizingthe data base the cost per access may be reduced.  however, the high cost of a reorganization prohibitsfrequent reorganizations.  this paper examines strategies for selecting the optimum reorganization points.cacm june, shneiderman, b..kdata base, reorganization, files, information retrieval.c.ca jb january ,   : pm